google is kicking off its 2004 college recruiting program and once again we are asking faculty to identify two or three of their top students bs ms phd for internships and full time positions at google we are looking for students with exceptional programming skills excellent algorithmic and analytical skills and a strong aptitude for building high performance scalable computer systems our recent work encompasses a broad spectrum of computer science research areas including large scale distributed systems design information retrieval natural language processing machine learning and data mining algorithms and data structures research and user interface research working at google provides the opportunity to solve challenging problems and to make a positive impact in the lives of tens of millions of users every day google is fun profitable and growing as fast as we can find exceptionally qualified engineers and researchers we have r&d offices at our headquarters in mountain view ca new york ny santa monica ca as well as new international offices in bangalore india and zurich switzerland
